# Flight Job(1) - Generate a job script from a predefined template

## Overview

~~~
$ flight job --help
  NAME:

    bin/job

  DESCRIPTION:

    Generate a job script from a predefined template

  COMMANDS:

    console
    copy-template  Generate a local copy of a template
    create-script  Generate a new script from a template
    help           Display global or [command] help documentation
    list-scripts   List the existing scripts
    list-templates List available templates
    show-template  Display details about a template
    submit-script  Start a job from a previously rendered script

  ALIASES:

    copy   copy-template
    cp     copy-template
    create create-script
    info   show-template
    ls     list-templates
    submit submit-script

  GLOBAL OPTIONS:

    -h, --help
        Display help documentation

    --version
        Display version information

    --verbose
        Display additional details

    --ascii
        Display a simplified version of the outpu
~~~

## List the Available Templates

The available templates can displayed using the `list-templates` command:

~~~
$ flight job list
+-------+-----------------+
| Index | Name            |
+-------+-----------------+
...
| 5     | howto-demo.sh   |
...
+-------+-----------------+
~~~

## View the Content of Template

Details about a template can be view with  the `show-template` command.

The template can be found by name:

~~~
$ flight job show-template howto-demo.sh
howto-demo.sh

  DESCRIPTION

  This is an example output of a template.
  The installed templates and indices will be different.

  LICENSE

  This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International License.

  COPYRIGHT

  Copyright (C) 2020 Alces Flight Ltd.
~~~

Or the template can be found by index:

~~~
$ flight job info 5
... same as above ...
~~~

## Creating a new Script

New `scripts` can be generated with the `create-script` command. This will step
you through various question prompts and generate a `script`.

~~~
flight job create-script howto-demo.sh
Working directory /home/%u
Set an output file for STDOUT job-%j.output
...
~~~

## Viewing Generated Scripts

A list of previously generated scripts is available with the `list-scripts`
command.

~~~
$ flight job list-scripts
+--------------------------------------+---------------+------------+
| ID                                   | Name          | Template   |
+--------------------------------------+---------------+------------+
...
| d91df58e-a2bb-486b-8372-174e1eaae1bf | howto-demo.sh | Howto Demo |
...
+--------------------------------------+---------------+------------+

~~~

## Submitting a New Job

New `jobs` can be submitted using the `submit-script` command.

~~~
flight job submit-script d91df58e-a2bb-486b-8372-174e1eaae1bf
Your job has been started!
~~~

## Copying a Template

Copying a template with the `copy-template` command has been deprecated and
will be removed in the next major release. Please use the `create-script`
command instead.
